Descriptor: Noise: Loud Music/Nighttime(Mark Date And Time) (NP1)
Resolution Description: The Department of Environmental Protection did not observe a violation of the New York City Air/Noise Code at the time of inspection and could not issue a notice of violation. If the problem still exists, please call 311 and file a new complaint. If you are outside of New York City, please call (212) NEW-YORK (212-639-9675).

Agency Name: Department of Health and Mental Hygiene
Resolution Description: The Department of Health and Mental Hygiene has sent official written notification to the Owner/Landlord warning them of potential violations and instructing them to correct the situation.  If the situation persists 21 days after your initial complaint, please make a new complaint.
Unfortunately, the behavior that you complained about does not violate any law or rule. As a result, no city agency has the jurisdiction to act on the matter.
The Department of Buildings investigated this complaint and referred it to the Fire Department of New York for further action.
The Police Department responded to the complaint and with the information available observed no evidence of the violation at that time.
